.TH "evergreen_mc_wait_for_idle" 9 "evergreen_mc_wait_for_idle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
evergreen_mc_wait_for_idle \- wait for MC idle callback.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" evergreen_mc_wait_for_idle
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon_device pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for the MC (memory controller) to be idle.
(evergreen+).
Returns 0 if the MC is idle, -1 if not.
